---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="FlyItalyADSB is Italy's first ADS-B flight tracking community. Non-profit, run by enthusiasts, infrastructure by Nesso Labs."
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-20 px-6 sm:px-12 lg:px-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto">

    <div class="mb-14">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Project</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-4">About</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed text-lg">
        FlyItalyADSB is Italy's first ADS-B flight tracking community.
        Born from a group of aviation enthusiasts, it has grown into a data collection
        infrastructure with global coverage and applications in scientific research.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Values -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        {[
          { icon: `<path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>`, title: 'Non-profit', desc: 'No commercial objective. The infrastructure is maintained by volunteers and Nesso Labs at no cost to users.' },
          { icon: `<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M2 12h20M12 2a15 15 0 0 1 0 20M12 2a15 15 0 0 0 0 20" stroke-linecap="round"/>`, title: 'Unfiltered data', desc: 'No FAA, LADD or BARR filters. Data is transmitted as received — including military aircraft via MLAT.' },
          { icon: `<path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75" stroke-linecap="round"/>`, title: 'Open source', desc: 'Stack based on readsb/tar1090/mlat-server by wiedehopf. All core software is public and freely reusable.' },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border" style="background:#0f1929;border-color:#1e3048">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4" style="background:#38bdf815;border:1px solid #38bdf830">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#38bdf8" stroke-width="1.5" set:html={item.icon}/>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100 mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- History -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-6">History</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          FlyItalyADSB was founded as a community of flight tracking enthusiasts in Italy.
          The network expanded progressively across the country — from the Alps to Sicily,
          from the Tyrrhenian Sea to the Adriatic coast — with receivers covering up to 400 km each.
          Over time, the feeder community grew beyond Italy to include receivers across Europe and beyond,
          giving FlyItalyADSB a genuinely global ground network.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2023, following the acquisition of ADS-B Exchange by JETNET (private equity),
          the non-profit tracking community fragmented. FlyItalyADSB maintained its independence
          and positioned itself alongside new community players such as adsb.lol, adsb.fi
          and airplanes.live — all based on the same open source stack, all non-profit, all unfiltered.
        </p>
        <p>
          Coverage today is global: beyond the ground network, the aggregation server
          receives data from adsb.lol and theairtraffic.com, extending the map worldwide.
          Italian MLAT remains a unique feature: FlyItalyADSB is the only network
          with active MLAT triangulation over Italy, including military flights.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2025, Mode-S data collected by the network became the foundation of the
          <a href="/en/ricerca/weather" class="text-sky-400 no-underline hover:text-sky-300">Weather 3.2</a>
          meteorological research project, which uses aircraft as high-altitude wind sensors
          to validate ERA5 reanalyses and IASI profiles.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Nesso Labs -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-6">Infrastructure</h2>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-start" style="background:#0f1929;border-color:#1e3048">
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100 mb-2">Nesso Labs</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            FlyItalyADSB's infrastructure — Kubernetes cluster, distributed storage, data pipelines —
            is managed by <a href="https://nessolabs.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-sky-400 no-underline">Nesso Labs</a>.
            FlyItalyADSB is the first "Nesso Data" project in the airspace mobility domain:
            collection, processing and distribution of public data —
            the same philosophy as the Nesso Equity project in the financial domain.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href="https://nessolabs.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
           class="shrink-0 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium no-underline transition-all"
           style="background:#ffffff08;color:#94a3b8;border:1px solid #ffffff14"
           onmouseover="this.style.background='#ffffff12'"
           onmouseout="this.style.background='#ffffff08'">
          nessolabs.it ↗
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contacts -->
    <section id="contatti" class="scroll-mt-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-6">Contact</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border" style="background:#0f1929;border-color:#1e3048">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-1 text-sm">Research inquiries</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Access to historical datasets, raw Mode-S data, MLAT CSV — for university or institutional research.
          </p>
          <a href="mailto:info@flyitalyadsb.com" class="text-sm text-sky-400 no-underline hover:text-sky-300">info@flyitalyadsb.com</a>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border" style="background:#0f1929;border-color:#1e3048">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-1 text-sm">GitHub</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Source code for custom components: readsb fork, mlat-server, flarm-ogn-to-sbs.
          </p>
          <a href="https://github.com/flyitalyadsb" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-sm text-sky-400 no-underline hover:text-sky-300">github.com/flyitalyadsb ↗</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border" style="background:#0a1320;border-color:#1e3048">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          For technical support on feeder setup or network questions,
          use the community GitHub Discussions channel or write to
          <a href="mailto:info@flyitalyadsb.com" class="text-sky-400 no-underline">info@flyitalyadsb.com</a>.
          We respond within 48 hours.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>
